lastExitPortLocation.description: The final exporting location for a shipment. This would be a port for sea, an airport for air, a terminal for rail, or a border post for land crossing.

exportCountry.description: The country from which the goods were originally exported, without any commercial transaction taking place in intermediate countries.

In addition to transport costs, this may include such elements as packing, documentation, loading, unloading, and insurance to the extent that they relate to the freight costs.

lastExitPortLocation.description: The final exporting location for a shipment. This would be a port for sea, an airport for air, a terminal for rail, or a border post for land crossing.

exportCountry.description: The country from which the goods were originally exported, without any commercial transaction taking place in intermediate countries.

In addition to transport costs, this may include such elements as packing, documentation, loading, unloading, and insurance to the extent that they relate to the freight costs.

masterPerson.description: The person responsible for the ship's safe and efficient operation, including cargo operations, navigation, crew management and for ensuring that the vessel complies with local and international laws, as well as company and flag state policies.

shipsSurgeonPerson.description: The person responsible for the health of the people aboard a ship at sea.

destinationPortCall.description: A destination port call for this shipment stage.

crewPersonEffect.description: The crew person effects for this shipment stage.

maritimeWaste.description: The maritime waste for this shipment stage.

ballastWaterSummary.description: A ballast water summary for this shipment stage.

iSPSRequirements.description: The ISPS (International Ship and Port Facility Security Code) requirements for this shipment stage.

maritimeHealthDeclaration.description: A maritime declaration of health for this shipment stage.

fuelConsumption.description: One or more fuel consumptions of this shipment stage.

OnCarriageShipmentStage.description: A class to describe one stage of movement in a transport of goods.

paidCashAmount.description: The amount given by the customer in cash or cash equivalents, if different from the payable amount. The Paid Amount = Paid Cash Amount - Cash Change Amount.

cashChangeAmount.description: The change returned to the customer when the paid cash amount is more than the payable amount.

receivedDate.description: The date on which this payment was received.

paidDate.description: The date on which this payment was made.

paidTime.description: The time at which this payment was made.

instructionID.description: An identifier for the payment instruction.

merchantID.description: An identifier for the merchant who handled the payment.

authorizationID.description: The authorization identifier for this payment.

transactionID.description: The transaction identifier for this payment.

paymentTerminalID.description: An identifier for the payment terminal used for this payment.

exchangeRate.description: The exchange rate applicable to this payment, if the payment currency differs from the document currency.

targetCurrencyBaseRate.description: In the case of a target currency with denominations of small value, the unit base.

calculationRate.description: The factor applied to the source currency to calculate the target currency.

mathematicOperatorCode.description: A code signifying whether the calculation rate is a multiplier or a divisor.

date.description: The date on which the exchange rate was established.

lineExtensionAmount.description: The monetary amount of an extended transaction line, net of tax and settlement discounts, but inclusive of any applicable rounding amount.

taxExclusiveAmount.description: The monetary amount of an extended transaction line, exclusive of taxes.

taxInclusiveAmount.description: The monetary amount including taxes; the sum of payable amount and prepaid amount.

allowanceTotalTaxInclusiveAmount.description: The total monetary amount of all allowances, inclusive of all taxes.

chargeTotalAmount.description: The total monetary amount of all charges.

payableRoundingAmount.description: The rounding amount (positive or negative) added to produce the line extension amount.

payableAlternativeAmount.description: The amount of the monetary total to be paid, expressed in an alternative currency.
